 (1599, 1, '2012-07-29 15:40:13', '2012-07-29 15:40:13', '[one_half]\n[toc title="Settings" hide="hide" show="show"]\n<ul>\n<li><a href="#CreateEventPost">Create event post</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="#Repeatable">Repeatable events</a></li>\n<li><a href="#Map">Add map location</a></li>\n<li><a href="#Layout">Event Post Layout</a></li>\n</ul></li>\n<li><a href="#Settings">Events Settings</a></li>\n<li><a href="#Categories">Customize events categories</a></li>\n<li><a href="#Categories">Slideshow Settings</a></li>\n\n</ul> \n[/toc]\n[/one_half] \n\n [one_half last=last] [toc title="Output" hide="hide" show="show"]\n<ul>\n<li><a href="#CalendarS">Event calendar shortcode</a></li>\n<li><a href="#Upcoming">Upcoming events  shortcode</a></li>\n<li><a href="#Widgets">Events widgets</a>\n<ul><li><a href="#Calendar">Calendar</a></li>\n<li><a href="#Upcoming">Upcoming events</a></li>\n<li><a href="#Countdown">Next event countdown</a></li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>[/toc]\n\n[/one_half] [clear]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/><br/> \n\n [one_third] <br/><h2><strong>Events</strong></h2>\nOn the next image and in your dashboard you can see new menu item called "Events". This is where you can organize and setup your events. [/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/events1.jpg" alt="" title="events" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1615 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n <h3> Create Event categories</h3>\n\nTo organize events you need to create events categories.\nYou can make it before, after or directly during the creation of the event posts. \n\nTo create event category go to <span style="color: #c62b02;"><strong> Events -> Event Categories</strong></span>\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/>\n<h3><span id="CreateEventPost">Create Event Post</span></h3>\n<strong>To create new event post, go to <span style="color: #c62b02;">Events -> Add new</span></strong>  \n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/> <br/>\n\n [one_third] \n<h3>Assign Event Category</h3>\nOn the right side you will see your events categories. You need to check in which category you want this event to be displayed.\n<hr/>\nIf you don’t have any categoies yet, then you need to create one.\n\nTo do this click <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>+ Add New Events Category</strong></span>.\nSet Category name and press Add New Events Category\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n[/one_third] \n [two_third last=last]  <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/categories1.jpg" alt="" title="categories" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1627 imgborder" />   [/two_third] [clear]\n\n\n<br/><br/>\n\n<h3>Set Event Date</h3>\nNow you need to set date & time for your event. \nYou can find this setting below the content editor in “Event date“ block. <br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/event_date.jpg" alt="" title="event_date" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1639 imgborder" />\n\n [one_third] <br/>Click on the date  field and caledar will appera where you can choose the date. \n\nOr you can simply type your date and time in this fields but <span style="color: #c62b02;"><strong>keep the formatting I.E.: \n07/31/2012\n12:00 AM</span>\n\n <span style="color: #c62b02;">This is most common issue.</strong></span> \n\n<span style="color: #c62b02;"><strong>Note: </strong></span>you can change time format in <strong>Settings-> General: Time Format</strong>.\n\n[/one_third]  [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/event_date_c.jpg" alt="" title="event_date_c" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1640" /> [/two_third] [clear]\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/><br/>\n\n<span id="Repeatable"><h3>Repeatable Event</h3></span>\nTo make event repeatable, you need to check <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>"Is repeating?"</strong></span> option. You can find it in the same Event date block. After that choose repetition interval.<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/repeatable.jpg" alt="" title="repeatable" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1655 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/><br/>\n\n<span id="Map"><h3>Event map</h3></span>\nNow you need to add event location.<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/map_01.jpg" alt="" title="map" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1653 imgborder" />\n<p>Click <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>New map</strong></span>. After that new options will appear.</p><br/>\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/map_02.jpg" alt="" title="map" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1653 imgborder" />\n\n1. Type your location and click <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Add</strong></span> button. You will see a pin with popup on the map.\n2. You can edit address in popup on the map by clicking “edit” link directly in popup.\n\n3. Add title for this location and press <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>save</strong></span> button to save location.\nNow you have a location for your event.<br/>\nYou can edit this location at any time. To do that rollover on location title and edit link will appear.\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/map_03.jpg" alt="" title="map" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1653 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/><br/>\n\n<h3>Additional Information</h3>\nYou can add additional information such as phone and address that will be used to display on event page and upcoming event widget.<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/additional.jpg" alt="" title="additional" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1650 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/><br/>\n\n  [one_half]  <span id="Layout"><h3>Set layout and sidebar \nfor event post.</h3></span>\nYou can set one of three possible layouts for event post: Full width, Left Sidebar and Right Sidebar. You can find this settings at the right side below the event categories. [/one_half] \n\n [one_half last=last]  <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/layout.jpg" alt="" title="layout" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1656 imgborder" /> [/one_half]  [clear]\n[notification type="notification_info_tiny"]If you want to have same sidebar and layout for all event posts you can set it in <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/events-global-settings/">global event settings.</a>[/notification] \n\n<br/>\nAlso there are additional widget area between the map and content. You can enable it by choosing <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Under title sidebar instance</strong></span> in “Title area settings” block below the editor.\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/underSidebar.jpg" alt="" title="underSidebar" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1649 imgborder" />\n[notification type="notification_info_tiny"]You can learn more about layouts, sidebars and widgets here.[/notification] \n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/><br/>\n\n\n<h3><span id="topic6">Slideshow Settings</span></h3>\nOur theme is extremely flexible and allows to set unique slideshow, with unique settigns for each post/page or taxonomies.\n\n[notification type="notification_info_tiny"]Please note that this settings will be applied ONLY for the specific page/post, where you set it and not for the other pages/posts.[/notification] \n\nTo set slideshow for specific page, scroll down to the "Slideshow options" block.\n\n1.<strong> Choose slideshow type</strong> - here you can between our custom JCycle or Revolution slideshows. By default it is set to use global settings (global settings is set in Theme Options ->Slideshows)\n\n2. Choose Revolution Slider (for revolution slider only) - you can create many revolution slideshows, so here you can choose which of revolution slideshows you would like to use.\n\n2. Set slideshow category (for jCycle only)\n\n3. and set max amount of slides for this slideshow (for jCycle only).\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/slideshow1.jpg" alt="slideshow" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3322 imgborder" />\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n\n    [one_third] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/publish.jpg" alt="" title="publish" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1654 imgborder" />    \n [/one_third]   [two_third last=last]    <h3>Publish</h3>\nAdd information for your event in editor and click publish button \nwhen you are done.  [/two_third] [clear]\n[notification type="notification_info_tiny"]You can learn how to create rockin content for your post/page here.[/notification] \n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><hr/><br/><br/>\n<h3><strong>How to Show my Events?</strong></h3>\nNow when you know how to create events post you need to learn how to show your events.\nTo show your events on site, you need to use event widgets and shortodes.<br/>\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/event-shortcodes/" target="" ]Event Shortcodes[/button]\n\nYou can also learn what is <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/sidebars-widgets/">widgets</a> and <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-use-shortcodes/">shotcodes</a> first.\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'How To Create Events', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'how-to-events', '', '', '2012-07-29 15:40:13', '2012-07-29 15:40:13', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=1599', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (1695, 1, '2012-08-11 23:17:45', '2012-08-11 23:17:45', '<br/>\n<h3 style="text-align:center;">You can set delay, effect type and randomize.</h3><br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/shortcodes_testimonials.png" alt="" title="shortcodes_testimonials" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2285 imgborder" />\n<pre><code>&#91;testimonials category="all" time="10" effect="fade" &#93;</code></pre>\n<br/>\n<hr /><br/>\n\n[one_third][testimonials category="all" time="15" randomize="on"  effect="fade" ][/one_third]\n[one_third][testimonials category="all" time="10" randomize="on"  effect="fade" ][/one_third]\n[one_third last=last][testimonials category="all" randomize="on" time="5" effect="fade" ][/one_third]\n\n[clear]\n<br/>\n<hr /><br/><br/>\n[two_third] [testimonials category="all" time="10" effect="fade" ] [/two_third] [one_third last=last] [testimonials category="all" time="10" effect="shuffle" ] [/one_third] [clear]\n', 'Testimonials Shortcode', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'testimonials-shortcode', '', '', '2012-08-11 23:17:45', '2012-08-11 23:17:45', '', 167, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=1695', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (1776, 1, '2012-08-13 19:28:29', '2012-08-13 19:28:29', '<br/><span id="00"><h2 style="font-size:40px; text-align:center; font-weight: 200;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2></span>\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n<br/>\n<h4>Installation & Upgrade</h4>\n<span style="font-size:14px; line-height: 36px;">01. <a href="#1-1">I’m having trouble uploading the theme: "The package could not be installed. The theme is missing the style.css stylesheet"</a>\n02. <a href="#1-2">What’s the easiest way to upgrade to the latest version?</a>\n03. <a href="#1-3">I’ve been trying to install the Dummy Content but when I press the button, nothing happens. What can I do?</a>\n\n</span>\n<br/>\n<h4>Settings</h4>\n<span style="font-size:14px; line-height: 36px;">01. <a href="#2-1">How to set a page as the front page?</a>\n02. <a href="#2-2">Is it possible to turn off responsiveness?</a>\n03. <a href="#2-3">How do I change WordPress log in page back to default?</a>\n04. <a href="#2-4">Im trying to translate this Theme, but no matter where I put the .PO and .MO I can not see my translations on the frontend.</a>\n05. <a href="#2-5">How can I change the day from which my week will start in calendar?</a>\n06. <a href="#2-6">How to make "News" page like in your live preview?</a>\n07. <a href="#2-7">How do I set a time and date for the count down timer for next event?</a>\n\n</span>\n<br/>\n<h4>Content Setup</h4>\n<span style="font-size:14px; line-height: 36px;">01. <a href="#3-1">How to add \'Latest Sermon:..\' block between slideshow and content area?</a>\n02. <a href="#3-2">At the bottom of my page it has the leave a comment box how do i rid my pages of that?</a>\n03. <a href="#3-3">How to add embeded video in slideshow?</a>\n04. <a href="#3-4">How to add/remove border to image?</a>\n05. <a href="#3-5">I would like to create the little picture boxes like the three on the home page, how do I do that?</a>\n06. <a href="#3-6">How do you use the shortcodes?</a>\n07. <a href="#3-7">How to remove the events from appearing in the top header section and replace with html objects?</a>\n08. <a href="#3-8">How to add a map to a page, like on your contact page? </a>\n09. <a href="#3-9">How do I change the url of each page created?</a>\n10. <a href="#3-10">How can I re-order the slide/gallery posts in my slideshow/gallery?</a>\n11. <a href="#3-11">I have no post or page names/titles on my site. Please help!</a>\n12. <a href="#3-12">How can I get Social Media Icons shortcodes to the widget area and also align them to center or right istead of left?</a>\n13. <a href="#3-13">Slideshow options are not working. Please Help!</a>\n14. <a href="#3-14">How to set event end time?</a>\n15. <a href="#3-15">My calendar gets crazy when the mouse passes on Saturday. How can I get rid of this?</a>\n16. <a href="#3-16">How do I add a download button to the audio player?</a>\n17. <a href="#3-17">How to embed a @font-face to ChurcHope?</a>\n18. <a href="#3-18">How to get 3 teasers on top of the sidebar and 2 articles beginning as shown on the Churchope example?</a>\n</span>\n<br/>\n<h4>Other</h4>\n<span style="font-size:14px; line-height: 36px;">01. <a href="#4-1">Is there a way to separate the color of the navigation bar from the color of the slider background? </a>\n02. <a href="#4-2">How do you change the link for the ribbon top right corner?</a>\n03. <a href="#4-3">How to remove the ribbon from top right corner?</a>\n04. <a href="#4-4">Curious about the breadcrumbs though … Im not getting them on my site, and dont see an option to turn on or off. </a>\n05. <a href="#4-5">Where can I find my secret API Key?</a>\n06. <a href="#4-6">Where can I check the changes implemented in the theme updates?</a>\n07. <a href="#4-7">How can I get refund?</a>\n08. <a href="#4-8">What is the best way to create image for "Color Header Image" use?</a>\n\n</span>\n<br/>\n<h4>CSS Tweaks</h4>\n<span style="font-size:14px; line-height: 36px;">01. <a href="#5-1">How to change the menu background color?</a>\n02. <a href="#5-2">How to change the menu text color?</a>\n03. <a href="#5-3">How to change the menu font size?</a>\n04. <a href="#5-4">How to apply a different font just for the main menu text?</a>\n05. <a href="#5-5">How can I center main menu?</a>\n06. <a href="#5-6">How do I change the font to bold in the menu?</a>\n07. <a href="#5-7">How to reduce top navigational menu height?</a>\n08. <a href="#5-8">How to change the hover color of the dropdown menu?</a>\n09. <a href="#5-9">How to remove post excerpt from \'most recent\' blog shortcode on homepage?</a>\n10. <a href="#5-10">I want to have the Header, the Slider and the Footer at my home page. How can I get rid of the main content area?</a>\n11. <a href="#5-11">How can I make the main content area at my home page smaller?</a>\n12. <a href="#5-12">How can I make the header for logo smaller/larger?</a>\n13. <a href="#5-13">How can I change the color of the teaser secondary line "more info"?</a>\n14. <a href="#5-14">How to remove Tags & Categories from post header?</a>\n15. <a href="#5-15">How can I remove image magnification feature from the thumbnails?</a>\n16. <a href="#5-16">How to change spacing in slideshow title?</a>\n17. <a href="#5-17">How to change the color of "DAYS", "HR", "MIN" and "SEC" at the header Next Event countdown section?</a>\n18. <a href="#5-18">How do I disable page title to appear in pages?</a>\n19. <a href="#5-19">How to increase font size in theme?</a>\n20. <a href="#5-20">How can I change content text line height?</a>\n21. <a href="#5-21">How do I increase the font size in the pages and posts general body text?</a>\n22. <a href="#5-22">Would want to increase the spacing between sentences for a easier read.</a>\n23. <a href="#5-23">I am trying to make the “send a message” contact form’s text black on the site.</a>\n24. <a href="#5-24">How to change the padding around the logo?</a>\n25. <a href="#5-25">I would like to add more space between the logo and the counter in the header.</a>\n26. <a href="#5-26">Is there a way to move the teaser title to bottom of featured image?</a>\n27. <a href="#5-27">How to change the color of the testimonial author in widget?</a>\n28. <a href="#5-28">How to change the color of the “buttons” shortcode?</a>\n29. <a href="#5-29">I need space between logo and widget.</a>\n30. <a href="#5-30">How can I change the color of the call to action button on the main slider?</a>\n31. <a href="#5-31">How can I adjust the padding on the slider?</a>\n</span>\n\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<br/><h2 style="text-align:center; font-weight: 700;">Installation & Upgrade</h2><br/>\n\n<span id="1-1"><h4>I’m having trouble uploading the theme to WordPress: "The package could not be installed. The theme is missing the style.css stylesheet"</h4></span>\n\nYou need to extract downloaded archive. It contains documentation and .psd files besides the theme files.\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="1-2"><h4>What’s the easiest way to upgrade to the latest version?</h4></span>\n\nFirst of all, you need to find out what version of theme is installed. You can check it in your <strong>Dashboard -> Appereance -> Themes</strong>.\n\nIf your theme version is less than v.1.9, then please download a new version of our theme:\n<ol><li> Go to downloads tab in your Themeforest account and simply download our theme again.</li>\n<li> Upload theme files via FTP. </li>\n<li> Don\'t forget to make a backup.</li></ol>\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Starting Version 1.9 we have developed a new functionality to update our theme.</strong></span>\nNow you can update Churchope theme directly from your dashboard.\n<ol>\n<li> Go to your Dashboard -> Theme Options -> Theme Updater.</li>\n<li> Fill in your ThemeForest User Account Information form.</li>\n\nTo get your Themeforest API key you need to:\n<ul><li> Go to Themeforest Dashboard.</li>\n<li> Click “My settings” tab.</li>\n<li> Click “API keys” menu on left side of page.</li>\n<li> Generate API key on this page and copy it.</li></ul>\n\n<li>After that you can find <strong>“Update”</strong> menu item in your Dashboard and update notification icon in your admin menu.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/update_01.jpg" alt="" title="update_01" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2962 imgborder" />\n</li>\n\n<li> Click any of them.</li>\n<li> Scroll to “Themes” section and click “Update Themes” button.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/update_02.jpg" alt="" title="update_02" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2963 imgborder" />\n\n</li></ol>\n\n\nHowever, update theme via FTP still works fine, you can use it if you prefer.\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Don’t forget to make backup</strong></span> of your theme files before update, if you modified theme files.\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="1-3"><h4>I’ve been trying to install the Dummy Content but when I press the button, nothing happens. What can I do?</h4></span>\n\nThis may be, because:\n<ol>\n<li> You didn’t installed theme correctly.</li>\n<li> You didn’t wait until it was installed.</li>\n<li> Some plugins can casue JS error. Try to turn off plugins if you have any installed.</li>\n</ol>\nAlso try to install our theme on clean WordPress installation.\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br/><h2 style="text-align:center; font-weight: 700;">Settings</h2><br/>\n\n<span id="2-1"><h4>How to set a page as the front page?</h4></span>\n\nYou need to set your Frontpage in <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Settings -> Reading</strong></span>\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/frontpage_setup.png" alt="" title="frontpage_setup" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1836 imgborder" />\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="2-2"><h4>Is it possible to turn off responsiveness?</h4></span>\n\n  [one_third] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/responsive.png" alt="" title="responsive" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1837 imgborder" /> [/one_third] \n  [two_third last=last]\n<br/><br/> You can tur on responsiveness from admin panel. \nGo to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> General</strong></span> and switch "Disable responsive" to on.  [/two_third] [clear]\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="2-3"><h4>How do I change WordPress log in page?</h4></span>\n\nYou can change design of login page easily without plugins. There are a lot of tutorials on the web on how to do it, i.e.:\n<a href="http://shailan.com/3004/customizing-wordpress-login-page-without-plugin/">http://shailan.com/3004/customizing-wordpress-login-page-without-plugin/</a>\n\nOur theme has an option to disable theme login page styling: <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Dashboard->Theme Options -> General -> Disable login page styling</strong></span>\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="2-4"><h4>Im trying to translate this Theme, but no matter where I put the .PO and .MO I can not see my translations on the frontend.</h4></span>\n\n\nYou need save your translation in theme root i.e. as <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>pt_BR.mo</strong></span> and after that edit wp-config.php in root of the site. Search for: <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>define (‘WPLANG’, ‘pt_BR’);</strong></span>\n\nYou can learn more here:\n<a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress_in_Your_Language">http://codex.wordpress.org/Installing_WordPress_in_Your_Language</a>\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="2-5"><h4>How can I change the day from which my week will start in calendar?</h4></span>\nYou should go to your <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Dashboard -> Settings -> General</strong></span> and set the necessary day in "Week Starts On" dropdown menu at the bottom.\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="2-6"><h4>How to make "News" page like in your live preview?</h4></span>\n<ul><li> Go to your <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Dashboard -> Pages -> Add new</strong></span> and set its title as "News".</li> \n<li>  Go to your <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Dashboard -> Settings -> Reading</strong></span> and select this page as your posts page.</li> \n</ul>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="2-7"><h4>How do I set a time and date for the count down timer for next event?</h4></span>\nYou should create your event first. The widget will take its settings automatically.\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br/><h2 style="text-align:center; font-weight: 700;">Content Setup</h2><br/>\n\n<span id="3-1"><h4>How to add \'Latest Sermon:..\' block between slideshow and content area, like on front page?</h4></span>\n\nThere are additional widget area between the header and content. You can enable it by choosing <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Under title sidebar instance</strong></span> in “Title area settings” block below the editor on any page/post or event post.\n\n<img class="alignnone imgborder" title="underSidebar" src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/underSidebar.jpg" alt="" />\nYou need to create custom sidebar for this area and place there your widgets. \n\nOn the Frontpage of our preview was used basic text widget with following content:\n<pre>&#91;three_fourth&#93;&lt;h2&gt;Latest Sermon: Not a Fan: The Open Invitation - February 12, 2012&lt;/h2&gt;   &#91;/three_fourth&#93; &#91;one_fourth last=last&#93; &#91;button type="churchope_button" url="http://themeforest.net/item/churchope-responsive-wordpress-theme/2708562" target="" &#93;Download Latest Sermon&#91;/button&#93; &#91;/one_fourth&#93; </pre>\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="3-2"><h4>At the bottom of my page it has the leave a comment box how do i rid my pages of that?</h4></span>\n\nThere are <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Screen options</strong></span> tab at the top in WP admin panel. Expand it and check <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Discussion</strong></span> and <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Comments</strong></span>. After that a new metabox will appear at the bottom of the page, where you can turn off comments.\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/screen-options.jpg" alt="" title="screen-options" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1805 imgborder" />\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="3-3"><h4>How to add embeded video in slideshow?</h4></span>\n\nStarting version 1.3 our theme has slideshow shortcode that gives you possibility to easily add video to slideshow and also provides pause/resume function. The slide ain\'t going to switch to the next one while video is playing. \n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/video_icon.jpg" alt="" title="video_icon" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1854 imgborder" />\n\nAll you need to do is click on video shortcode button/icon, at the editor panel in visual mode, and paste your url in popup:\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/video.jpg" alt="" title="video" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1844 imgborder" />\n \n<br/>Sample code of slide with video:\n<pre><code>&#91;one_half&#93;\n&lt;h3 class="entry-title"&gt;YOUTUBE, VIMEO OR SELFHOSTED VIDEOS&lt;/h3&gt;\nSed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem accusantium doloremque laudantium, totam rem aperiam, eaque ipsa quae ab illo inventore veritatis et quasi architecto beatae vitae dicta sunt explicabo. Nemo enim ipsam voluptatem quia voluptas sit aspernatur aut odit aut fugit.\n&#91;/one_half&#93;\n&#91;one_half last=last&#93;&#91;thvideo w="100%" h="260px"&#93;http://player.vimeo.com/video/34783883&#91;/thvideo&#93; &#91;/one_half&#93;</code></pre>\n\n[notification type="notification_info_tiny"]This shortcode works only for slideshow posts.[/notification]\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="3-4"><h4>How to add/remove border to image?</h4></span>\n\nIf you add image using standart WordPress uploader it will be inserted into post with frame. To remove this frame you need to switch to HTML mode in editor and remove this class: <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>imgborder</strong></span>\n\nExample of an image with frame:<pre><code>&lt;img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/.../sample.jpg" alt="" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1805 <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>imgborder"</strong></span> /&gt;</code></pre>\n\nIf you need to add frame to image, add class <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>imgborder</strong></span>.\nAnother example of an image with frame:<pre><code>&lt;img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/.../sample.jpg" alt="" class="<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>imgborder"</strong></span> /&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="3-5"><h4>I would like to create the little picture boxes like the three on the home page, how do I do that?</h4></span>\n\nThree boxes on front page is a teaser shortcodes.\nWhen you edit page/post switch to visual mode and you’ll see shortcode buttons(icons) on editor panel. Click on teaser shortcode button. Popup with options will appear.\n\nThere are two ways to make teaser:\n\n1. Using post/page: <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>“Choose a template”</strong></span>.\nIn this case it will use post title and featured image for teaser title and image.\n\n2. Using direct link to image <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>“Type your image URL here”</strong></span>.\n\nCheck this page to see how teaser shortcode should look like:\n<a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/shortcodes/teasers/">http://churchope.themoholics.com/shortcodes/teasers/</a>\n\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="3-6"><h4>How do you use the shortcodes?</h4></span>\n\nThere a shotcode buttons/icons in visual mode when you edit post/page. Simply click the one you need. You’ll see popup with different option for diferent shortcodes.\nCheck this page: <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/shortcodes/">http://churchope.themoholics.com/shortcodes/</a>\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="3-7"><h4>How to remove the events from appearing in the top header section and replace with html objects?</h4></span>\n\nIt is additional widget area in header.\nGo to Appearance -> Widgets, seach for <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>"Header sidebar"</strong></span> at the right side, remove events countodwn widget and drag in widget that you need from the left side.\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/header_sidebar.png" alt="" title="header_sidebar" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1838 imgborder" />\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="3-8"><h4>How to add a map to a page, like on your contact page?</h4></span>\n\nYou can find <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>New map</strong></span> button just below the editor when you edit page.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/map.jpg" alt="" title="map" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2124 imgborder" />\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Note:</strong></span> This feature was added in version 1.3 of our theme.\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="3-9"><h4>How do I change the url of each page created?</h4></span>\nYou can do it in two ways:\n\n<ul><li> Go to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Dashboard->Pages->All Pages</strong></span>, click "Quick Edit" and edit the "Slug" field.</li>\n<li> Go to a single page and click the "Edit" button just under the title field.\n</li></ul>\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="3-10"><h4>How can I re-order the slide/gallery posts in my slideshow/gallery?</h4></span>\nYou should edit publish time or date of your slideshow/gallery post.\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="3-11"><h4>I have no post or page names/titles on my site. Please help!</h4></span>\nTitle is not displayed when the slideshow is setup on the post/page because it covers the same area.\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="3-12"><h4>How can I get Social Media Icons shortcodes to the widget area and also align them to center or right istead of left?</h4></span>\n<ol><li> Go to the editing area of your page/post and place the necessary social medias between the \n<pre><code>&lt;div style="text-align:right"&gt; ...here... &lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>\n tags using shortcodes.</li>\n<li> Go to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Dashboard -> Appearance -> Widgets</strong></span> and drag the "Text" widget to necessary sidebar at the right of the page.</li>\n<li> Copy & paste the resulting code to the "Text" widget and click "Save".</li>\n</ol>\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="3-13"><h4>Slideshow options are not working. Please Help!</h4></span>\nMake sure that you make them in a proper way: \n\n<ol><li>You can set <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/slideshow-settings/">global slideshow</a> at your <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Dashboard -> Theme Options -> Slideshows</strong></span></li>\n\n<li>Or <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-setup-slideshow/">single page slideshow</a> at a certain page in the "Slideshow Options" block, which you can find scrolling down the page.\nYou can learn here <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-setup-slideshow/#topic12">"How to Add Slideshow to specific page/post"</a>.</li>\n\n<li>Also check the permissions of your wordpress files. They should be 644(files), 755(directories).</li>\n</ol>\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="3-14"><h4>How to set event end time?</h4></span>\nYou can see events functionality in our documentaion: <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-events/">http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-events/</a>\n\nWe are currently working on a complicated events system plugin but it will be available (maybe in a month or two) as a separate product. Making a proper event system requires no less effort than creating a theme.\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="3-15"><h4>My calendar gets crazy when the mouse passes on Saturday. How can I get rid of this?</h4></span>\nMost likely, you have zoomed page in your browser. Try to press ctrl+0.\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="3-16"><h4>How do I add a download button to the audio player?</h4></span>\nPlease check this topic: <a href="http://help.themoholics.com/discussion/comment/1094#Comment_1094">http://help.themoholics.com/discussion/comment/1094#Comment_1094</a>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="3-17"><h4>How to embed a @font-face to ChurcHope?</h4></span>\nPlease check this topic: <a href="http://help.themoholics.com/discussion/545/how-to-embed-a-font-face-to-churchope#Item_6">http://help.themoholics.com/discussion/545/how-to-embed-a-font-face-to-churchope#Item_6</a>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="3-18"><h4>How to get 3 teasers on top of the sidebar and 2 articles beginning as shown on the Churchope example?</h4></span>\nPlease check this topic: <a href="http://help.themoholics.com/discussion/612/how-to-get-3-teasers-on-top-of-the-sidebar-and-2-articles-beguining-as-shown-on-the-churchope-exempl#Item_2">http://help.themoholics.com/discussion/612/how-to-get-3-teasers-on-top-of-the-sidebar-and-2-articles-beguining-as-shown-on-the-churchope-exempl#Item_2</a>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br/><h2 style="text-align:center; font-weight: 700;">Other</h2><br/>\n\n<span id="4-1"><h4>Is there a way to separate the color of the navigation bar from the color of the slider background?</h4></span>\n\nAdd next CSS rule to Dashboard->Theme options->Custom Styles\n<pre><code>.mainmenu {background-color:green}</code></pre>\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="4-2"><h4>How do you change the link for the ribbon top right corner?</h4></span>\n\nYou can find it at Dashboard->Theme Options->Header: "Call to action header ribbon URL".\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="4-3"><h4>How to remove the ribbon from top right corner?</h4></span>\n\nGo to Dashboard->Theme Options->Header: and make  <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>"Call to action header ribbon URL"</strong></span> field completely  <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>empty</strong></span>, even without spaces!\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="4-4"><h4>Curious about the breadcrumbs though … Im not getting them on my site, and dont see an option to turn on or off.</h4></span>\n\nWe decided to use this must have plugin for breadcrumbs: <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wordpress-seo/">http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wordpress-seo/</a>\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/seoPlugin.jpg" alt="" title="seoPlugin" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1852 imgborder" />\n\nYou can activate breadcrumbs on “Internal links” page of this plugin.\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/yoast.jpg" alt="" title="yoast" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1851 imgborder" />\n\nThis plugin is free and have a lot of nice features, so we recommend to use it. \n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/totop.png" alt="" title="totop" /><a href="#00">to Top</a>\n\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="4-5"><h4>Where can I find my secret API Key?</h4></span>\nYou should follow this link: <a href="http://support.envato.com/index.php?/Knowledgebase/Article/View/280/0/what-is-the-envato-marketplace-api">Envanto Knowledgebase</a>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="4-6"><h4>Where can I check the changes implemented in the theme updates?</h4></span>\nYou can check updates list at the very bottom of the <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/churchope-responsive-wordpress-theme/2708562">product page.</a>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="4-7"><h4>How can I get refund?</h4></span>\nWe are only the authors on envato marketplace. We only provide technical support for our themes.\n\nAll questions regarding billing, refund etc should be addressed to envato support: <a href="http://support.envato.com/">http://support.envato.com/</a>\n\nYou can also check their knowledgebase: <a href="http://support.envato.com/index.php?/Knowledgebase/Article/View/256/0/can-i-get-a-refund-for-an-item-i-have-purchased.">http://support.envato.com/index.php?/Knowledgebase/Article/View/256/0/can-i-get-a-refund-for-an-item-i-have-purchased.</a>\n\nIt is not easy  to receive refund, because there should be a good reason.\nSo we suggest you to ask presale questions first to make sure that this theme will work for you, instead of asking for refund in future.\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="4-8"><h4>What is the best way to create image for "Color Header Image" use?</h4></span>\nTry to use a JPEG type of image with a low quality - around 40-50.\nYou can follow <a href="http://www.tutorial9.net/tutorials/photoshop-tutorials/saving-images-for-the-web/">this link</a> for more information.\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br/><h2 style="text-align:center; font-weight: 700;">CSS Tweaks</h2><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-1"><h4>How to change the menu background color?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.mainmenu {background-color:#ffffff} </code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-2"><h4>How to change the menu text color?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.sf-menu > li > a {color:#0076C7}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-3"><h4>How to change the menu font size?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.sf-menu > li > a  {font-size:20px}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-4"><h4>How to apply a different font just for the main menu text?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.sf-menu > li > a {font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-5"><h4>How can I center main menu?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.main_menu {float:none!important}\n.main_menu .sf-menu {margin:0 auto;display:table}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-6"><h4>How do I change the font to bold in the menu?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.main_menu {\nfont-weight: 700;\n}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-7"><h4>How to reduce top navigational menu height?</h4></span>\nAdd next rules to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.main_menu { min-height: 20px; height: 40px; }\n.sf-menu > li, .sf-menu > li > a { height: 38px; }\n.sf-menu > li:hover > ul, .sf-menu > li.sfHover > ul { top: 38px; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-8"><h4>How to change the hover color of the dropdown menu?</h4></span>\nAdd next rule to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.sf-menu ul li:hover, .sf-menu ul li.sfHover { background: red; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-9"><h4>How to remove post excerpt from \'most recent\' blog shortcode on homepage?</h4></span>\nAdd next rule to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.home .entry-content p { display: none; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-10"><h4>I want to have the Header, the Slider and the Footer at my home page. How can I get rid of the main content area?</h4></span>\nAdd next rules to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.home #main, .home #sticky-footer-push { display: none; }</code></pre>\n\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-11"><h4> How can I make the main content area at my home page smaller?</h4></span>\nAdd next rules to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.home #main { padding-bottom: 10px; padding-top: 23px; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-12"><h4>How can I make the header for logo smaller/larger?</h4></span>\nAdd next rules to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.header_top { margin-top: -35px; margin-bottom: -32px; }</code></pre>\n\nor\n\n<pre><code>.header_top { padding-top: 20px; padding-bottom: 20px; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-13"><h4>How can I change the color of the teaser secondary line "more info"?</h4></span>\nAdd next rule to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.teaser_more { background-color: green !important; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-14"><h4>How to remove Tags & Categories from post header?</h4></span>\nAdd next rule to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.blogtitles p { display: none; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-15"><h4>How can I remove image magnification feature from the thumbnails?</h4></span>\nAdd next rule to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.imghover { display: none; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-16"><h4>How to change spacing in slideshow title?</h4></span>\nAdd next rule to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>.cycle_content h3.entry-title { line-height: 1.3em; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-17"><h4>How to change the color of "DAYS", "HR", "MIN" and "SEC" at the header Next Event countdown section?</h4></span>\nAdd next rules to your custom styles:\n\n<pre><code>header .grid_6 .widget_event li .descr { color: red; opacity: 1; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-18"><h4>How do I disable page title to appear in pages?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>#pagetitle {\ndisplay: none;\n}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n<span id="5-19"><h4>How to increase font size in theme?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>body {font-size:20px}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-20"><h4>And how can I change content text line height?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.entry-content {line-height:150%}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-21"><h4>How do I increase the font size in the pages and posts general body text?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.entry-content {font-size:20px}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-22"><h4>Would want to increase the spacing between sentences for a easier read.</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>#main .grid_8 h6, #main .grid_12 h6 {\nline-height: 150%;\nword-spacing:10px;\n}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-23"><h4>I am trying to make the “send a message” contact form’s text black on the site.</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>input::-webkit-input-placeholder, select::-webkit-input-placeholder, textarea::-webkit-input-placeholder {\n    color:    black;\n}\ninput:-moz-placeholder, select:-moz-placeholder, textarea:-moz-placeholder {\n    color:    black;\n}\ninput:-ms-input-placeholder, select:-ms-input-placeholder, textarea:-ms-input-placeholder {\n    color:    black;\n}\n\ninput, select, textarea {\n    color:    black;\n}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-24"><h4>How to change the padding around the logo?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.logo span, .logo img {\npadding: 15px 0;\n}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-25"><h4>I would like to add more space between the logo and the counter in the header.</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>header .widget-title, header .expiration-timer { float: right !important; }</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-26"><h4>Is there a way to move the teaser title to bottom of featured image?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.teaser_title {top:50%}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-27"><h4>How to change the color of the testimonial author in widget?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.testimonial_author {color:red !important}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-28"><h4>How to change the color of the “buttons” shortcode?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.churchope_button {background-color:greean}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-29"><h4>I need space between logo and widget.</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>header .widget {float:right}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<span id="5-30"><h4>How can I change the color of the call to action button on the main slider?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>a.cycle_btn {\nbackground-color:blue;\nbox-shadow: 0 1px 0 0 navy, 0 2px 0 0 navy, 0 3px 0 0 navy;\n}</code></pre>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<span id="5-31"><h4>How can I adjust the padding on the slider?</h4></span>\n\nAdd following code in Theme Options -> Custom Styles:\n\n<pre><code>.bgimage { padding: 50px 0 60px; }</code></pre>\n\nAlso, you will need to change auto resize height values at /js/script.js search for: 110 and adjust it two times.\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<br/><h2 style="font-size:30px; text-align:center; font-weight: 200;">Still have a questions?</h2>\n<h4 style="text-align:center;">We\'ll be glad to give you an answers at our help forum!</h4>\n<center>[button type="churchope_button" url="http://help.themoholics.com" target="" ]Ask[/button]</center>', 'FAQ', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'faq', '', '', '2015-05-06 21:36:28', '2015-05-06 13:36:28', '', 0, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=1771', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (1866, 1, '2012-08-14 21:17:16', '2012-08-14 21:17:16', '<br/><h2 style="text-align: center; font-size: 46px; font-weight: 200;">Welcome</h2>\n<h4 style="text-align:center;"> to the "ChurcHope" WordPress Theme Online Documentation</h4> [clear]\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<strong><h3>THEME INSTALLATION</h3></strong>\n\nThe first step is installing your theme. There are two ways to install your theme and you need to choose the method which suits you most – via  WordPress dashboard or FTP. The easier method is via WordPress dashboard but there are certain situations when it is impossible so we are going to name both.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/theme-installation/" target="" ]Install your WordPress theme[/button]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n<br/>\n [two_third] <h3 style="font-weight: bold;">GENERAL & GLOBAL OPTIONS OVERVIEW</h3><br/>\n [one_fourth]  <ul>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/general-options/">General</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/header-settings/">Header</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/slideshow-settings/">Slideshow</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/blog-settings/">Blog</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/sidebars-settings/">Sidebars</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/galleries-settings/">Galleries</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/events-global-settings/">Events</a></li>\n</ul>  [/one_fourth] \n\n  [one_fourth last=last]  <ul>\n\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/testimonials-settings/">Testimonials</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/footer-settings/">Footer</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/custom-styles/">Custom Styles</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/recaptcha/">reCaptcha</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/faq/#1-2">Theme Updater</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/dummy-content/">Dummy Content</a></li>\n</ul>  [/one_fourth][clear]   [/two_third] \n\n [one_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignnone imgborder" />\n [/one_third] [clear]\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<strong><h3>CONTENT SETUP</h3></strong><br/>\n\n [one_third] <h4>Pages</h4>\nYou can find all information about pages.From how to create page to how to setup different layouts, sidebars and even slideshow for page.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-create-page/" target="" ]Setup Pages[/button] \n<br/>\n<h4>Posts</h4>\nYou can find all information about post. From how to create post to how to create blog page to display your posts.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-create-posts/" target="" ]Setup Posts[/button] [/one_third] \n\n [one_third] <h4>Galleries</h4>\nYou can find all information about galleries. From how to create, to how to display your gallery posts in your theme using shortcodes and widgets.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-create-gallery/" target="" ]Setup Galleries[/button] \n<br/>\n<h4>Slideshows</h4>\nYou can find all information about slideshow. From how to create slideshow post to how to setups slideshow for pages/posts.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-setup-slideshow/" target="" ]Setup Slideshow[/button] [/one_third] \n\n[one_third last=last] \n<h4>Testimonials</h4>\nYou can find all information about testimonials. From how to create testimonials post to how to display testimonials in your theme.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-create-testimonials/" target="" ]Setup Testimonials[/button] \n<br/>\n<h4>Events</h4>\nYou can find all information about events, from how to create event post to how to display events in your theme using shortcodes and widgets.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/how-to-events" target="" ]Setup Events[/button][/one_third] [clear]\n\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<strong><h3>SHORTCODES</h3></strong>\n\nShortcodes are integrated in default editor and you can add any of them in just a couple of clicks. So you don’t need to remember all these shortcodes anymore.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/how-to-use-shortcodes" target="" ]Learn how to Use the Shortcodes[/button]\n\n<br/>\n\n [one_third]<ul> \n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/blog-shortcode/">Blog</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/contact-form-builder/">Contact form Builder</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/teasers-shortcode/">Teasers</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/gallery-shortcode/">Gallery</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/pricing-plans-shortcode/">Pricing plans</a></li> \n</ul>[/one_third] \n\n [one_third]<ul> \n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/social-shortcodes/">Social Links & Buttons</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/notification-shortcodes/">Notifications</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/testimonials-shortcode/">Testimonials</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/toggles-shortcode/">Toggles</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/tabs-shortcode/">Tabs</a></li>\n</ul> [/one_third] \n\n [one_third last=last] <ul>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/event-shortcodes/">Events</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/buttons-shortcode/">Buttons</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/slideshow-video-shortcode/">Slideshow Video</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/column-shortcodes/">Columns</a></li>\n<li>Other</li>\n</ul> [/one_third] [clear]\n\n\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n\n<strong><h3>OTHER IMPORTANT STUFF</h3></strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/sidebars-widgets/">Sidebars & Widgets</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/wordpress-menus/">Navigational menus</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/theme-translation/">Theme Translation</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/custom-styles">Custom styles</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/breadcrumbs/">Breadcrumbs</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<strong><h3>CUSTOMIZE THEME LOOK</h3></strong>\nIn this section we will talk about WordPress default theme customizer. This feature is available starting version 3.4 of WordPress. It allows you to customize theme options even before activating a new theme.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/customize-theme-look/" target="" ]Customize my theme look[/button]\n\n\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<strong><h3>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTOINS</h3></strong>\nWe also have a FAQ section, where you can find answers to the most common questions.\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://churchope.themoholics.com/faq" target="" ]View FAQ[/button]\n\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n\n<strong><h3>HELP FORUM</h3></strong>\nStill have a questions? We’ll be glad to give you an answers at our help forum!\n\n[button type="simple_button_link" url="http://help.themoholics.com" target="" ]Help Forum[/button]', 'Online Documentation', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'online-documentation', '', '', '2015-05-06 21:37:22', '2015-05-06 13:37:22', '', 0, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=1866', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (1960, 1, '2012-08-25 17:10:51', '2012-08-25 17:10:51', '[one_third] <br/><span id="Settings"><h2><strong>Events Global Settings</strong></h2></span>\nOn the next image and in your dashboard you can see menu item called "Events" in "Theme Options". This is where you can setup some global settings for your events. [/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/event_settings_menu.jpg" alt="" title="event_settings_menu" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1725 imgborder" />[/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<span id="WhatIsGlobal"><h3>Introduction</h3></span>\nUsing global settings you can set, lets say same layout and sidebar for all event posts that you will create. But you can always overwrite this setting for each post. There are lots of setting below the editor, or at the left side, when you edit events post. <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/how-to-events/#Layout">Check layout settings for event post.</a>\n\n<span style="color: #c62b02;"><strong>Note:</strong></span> To make global settings work you need to make sure that, for example, event post layout setting is set to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Use global</strong></span> or <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Use global Sidebar</strong></span><br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/customSidebar.jpg" alt="" title="globalSidebar" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1969 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n\n<span id="LayoutEventListing"><h3>Layout settings for events listing</h3></span>\nFirst two options controls position of sidebar for events listings and which instance of sidebars to use. Our theme is scalable and can be used with (Left Sidebar and Right Sidebar) or without sidebars (Full width).\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/event_listing_sidebar.jpg" alt="" title="event_listing_sidebar" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1723 imgborder" />\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar position for events listing</strong></span> - this option allows you to choose where the sidebar should be placed at events category pages: on the left, right side or completely removed (full width).\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar for events listing</strong></span> - select which of the sidebar you would like to use at events category pages. You can learn how to create sidebar here: <a href="">Setup sidebars</a>\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n\n<span id="LayoutEventPosts"><h3>Layout settings for single event posts</h3></span>\nFor single event post you can customize next options:\n <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar position for single event post</strong></span> - this option allows you to choose where the sidebar should be placed at events posts: on the left, right side or completely removed (full width).\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar for single event post</strong></span> - select which of the sidebar you would like to use at single event posts. You can learn how to create sidebar here: <a href="">Setup sidebars</a>\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/event_post_sidebar.jpg" alt="" title="event_post_sidebar" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1724 imgborder" />\n\n[notification type="notification_info_tiny"]You can overwrite global settings and set custom layout and sidebar for each event post[/notification] \n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n\n [one_half]<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/map_settings.jpg" alt="" title="map_settings" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1727 imgborder" />  [/one_half] \n\n [one_half last=last]<span id="Map"><h3>Map Settings</h3></span>\n\nThis options allows you to set following options for google map on events pages:<br/>\n\n <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Map types</strong></span> - Allow your readers to change the map type (street, satellite, or hybrid)\n\n <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Scroll wheel zoom</strong></span> - Enable zoom with the mouse scroll wheel\n\n <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Tooltips</strong></span> - Show marker titles as a "tooltip" on mouse-over\n\n <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Language</strong></span> - Use a specific for map controls (defaults - browser language). Read Google Maps API docs for more info.[/one_half]  [clear]\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<span id="Slug"><h3>Custom Slugs</h3></span>\nAlso you can set your custom slugs for events post and taxonomy.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/event_slug.jpg" alt="" title="event_slug" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1726 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'Events Global Settings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'events-global-settings', '', '', '2012-08-25 17:10:51', '2012-08-25 17:10:51', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=1960', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (1981, 1, '2012-08-27 21:59:29', '2012-08-27 21:59:29', ' [one_third] <br/><h2><strong>General Settings</strong></h2>\nIn General Settings you can find options related to the entire site such as fonts, favicon, content colors and more.<br/>\nTo edit general settings navigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> General</strong></span> page at your Dashboard.[/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions1.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1985 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Choose a Font</h3>\n\nYou can change headings font for the whole website. Simply choose from hundreds of available google fonts from the dropdown.<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/google_font.jpg" alt="" title="google_font" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1986 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Check to disable Google Fonts </h3>\n\nIf you, for some reason, don\'t want to use google fonts, then you will want to turn on this option to disable it. After that default font will be used.<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/disable_google_fonts.jpg" alt="" title="disable_google_fonts" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1990 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Favicon URL</h3>\n\nFavicon is a small icon that browsers use for your website to make it more recognizable, for example in your bookmarks or history. If a website has a favicon then you will usually see it to the left of the address bar or in browser tab. You need to type full URL to your favicon.ico (i.e.: http://Themoholics.com/images/favicon.ico)<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/favicons.jpg" alt="" title="favicons" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1988 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Disable login page styling</h3>\n\nBy default login page has our custom styling. If you want to disable it and switch to the default WordPress login page styling, simply turn on this option.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/login_page_styling.jpg" alt="" title="login_page_styling" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1989 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Disable responsiveness </h3>\n\nOur website has responsive design what means it change it look on different resolutions to improve usablility and also make it fully functional on devices. If you don\'t want it to change layout for different resolutions and stay fixed, then you can turn on this option.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/disable_responsivenes.jpg" alt="" title="disable_responsivenes" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1987 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Color settings</h3>\n\nThis options allows you to choose colors for the following content (on the light background by default) elements: <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>texts, headings and links</strong></span>.\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/content_colors.jpg" alt="" title="content_colors" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1991 imgborder" />\n\n[notification type="notification_info_tiny"] You can also edit colors for footer and header elements in <a href="">Footer</a> and <a href="">Header settings</a>, respectively. [/notification]\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'General Options', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'general-options', '', '', '2012-08-27 21:59:29', '2012-08-27 21:59:29', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=1981', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (2004, 1, '2012-08-28 00:01:12', '2012-08-28 00:01:12', ' [one_third] <br/><h2><strong>Header Settings</strong></h2>\nThe Header tab holds options which are all about configuring your header part of website, including logo, top line, slideshow area and menu. \n<br/>\nTo edit Header settings navigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> Header</strong></span> page at your Dashboard.[/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions1.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1985 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Use custom logo image</h3>\nTo use your own logo simply click "Choose file" button in the "Use custom logo image" block, then select to upload your logo image. \n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/logo.jpg" alt="" title="logo" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2016 imgborder" />\n\n<h3>Hide logo image</h3> \nIn case you do not wish to use a logo you can hide it by setting "Hide logo image" option to "On". \n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/hide_logo.jpg" alt="" title="hide_logo" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2015 imgborder" /> \n\n[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Use custom pattern image for header section </h3>\nHere you can upload and set pattern image for the top line of the website, where the logo is located. Click "Choose file", browse for your pattern image and upload it.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/pattern_top1.jpg" alt="" title="pattern_top1" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2020 imgborder" />\n\n<br/>\n<h3>Custom pattern settings</h3>\nAfter you uploaded your pattern image, you can adjust it position and choose whether it will be repeatable or not.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/pattern_top.jpg" alt="" title="pattern_top" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2019 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Use custom pattern image for color header section </h3>\nSame as for logo area, you can set background image or pattern for slideshow and menu area. This image will be used for all website pages and can <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>NOT</strong></span> be set specifically for each page.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/pattern_header.jpg" alt="" title="pattern_header" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2017 imgborder" />\n\n<br/>\n<h3>Custom pattern settings</h3>\nAfter you uploaded your pattern image, you can adjust it position and choose whether it will be repeatable or not.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/pattern_header2.jpg" alt="" title="pattern_header2" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2018 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Call to action header ribbon URL </h3>\nThis field is responsible for the fancy call to action ribbon that you can find at the top of the website. You are able to set custom link to your ribbon, or remove ribbon. <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>To remove call to action ribbon</strong></span>, simply leave this field completely empty, even without spaces!\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/ribbon.jpg" alt="" title="ribbon" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2012 imgborder" />\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Align menu to left </h3>\nThis option allows you to choose menu alignment. By default it aligned to the right side, but by turning “On” this option you can set left alignment for the menu.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/alignMenu.jpg" alt="" title="alignMenu" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2013 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n\n[clear]\n [one_half] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/colors.jpg" alt="" title="colors" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2014 imgborder" /> [/one_half] \n [one_half last=last] \n<h3>Header Color Settings</h3>\nThis options allows you to choose colors for the following header elements: \n\n<ol>\n<li> Top (logo area) line background color</li>\n<li> Top line text color</li>\n<li> Slideshow and menu area background color</li>\n<li> Slideshow and menu text color</li> \n</ol><br/>[totop] to Top [/totop]  [/one_half] [clear]\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>How to change other theme Colors?</h3>\nIf you need to change some other colors you can check <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/faq">CSS Tweaks</a> section in our <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/faq">FAQ</a>.', 'Header Settings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'header-settings', '', '', '2012-08-28 00:01:12', '2012-08-28 00:01:12', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=2004', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (2023, 1, '2012-08-28 23:05:27', '2012-08-28 23:05:27', ' [one_third] <br/><h2><strong>Slideshow Settings</strong></h2>\nUsing global settings you can set settings for slideshow that will be used by default for each page/post. You can set such settings as autoplay, pause, nevigation arrows, slideshow height, etc.<br/>\nTo edit slideshow settings navigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> Slideshow</strong></span> page at your Dashboard.[/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions1.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1985 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<h3>Introduction</h3>\nUsing global settings you can set settings for slideshow that will be used by default for each page/post. So it is best to create global slideshow if you want to have same slideshow on every page of your website. But if you want to create different slideshow for different pages then you need to disbale slideshow in this settings and set it localy for each page/post. \n\nIf you set slideshow localy in page settings, global slideshow options like category, how many slides to display, timeout, speed, etc. will be ignored and used from local page settings. \nTo make global settings work you need to make sure that, for example, slideshow type in page/posts settings is set to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Use global</strong></span>.\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Basic Slideshow Settings</h3>\nTo make slideshow work you need to set slideshow type and category. Our theme comes only with two slideshow types or custom Jcycle slideshow & Revolution, third option is to disbale slideshow.\nFor Revolutions slideshow, you can choose which of slideshows to use. <strong>All other options at this page is fo JCycle slideshow only. To setup Revolution Slider navigate to Dashboard -> Revolution Slider</strong>\nFor JCycle slideshow you need to choose what category to use and set how many slides to display. But note that all of these settings will be set only for global slideshow.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/choose_slideshowtype.jpg" alt="" title="choose_slideshowtype" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2029 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Slideshow Timeout and Speed</h3>\nHere you can set slideshow transition speed (speed of animation) and slideshow timeout (how long it will wait before switch to the next slide). \n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/slideshow_speed.jpg" alt="" title="slideshow_speed" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2031 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Slideshow Pause and Autoplay</h3>\nSet slideshow pause to "On" if you want slideshow to be paused when you roll mouse over slideshow.\nYou can also turn on/off slideshow autoplay.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/slideshow_pause.jpg" alt="" title="slideshow_pause" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2030 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Setting added in v 1.4 of our theme</h3><br/>\n<h4>Next, Previous navigation arrows</h4>\nYou can choose whether to show navigation arrows in slideshow or not. Arrows will be displayed only for high resolutions and will be replaced for devices.\n<br/>\n<h4>Slideshow fixed height</h4>\nNow you can make fixed height for slideshow easily by setting it height in <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>pixels</strong></span>.\n<br/>\n<h4>Remove top and bottom paddings from slideshow </h4>\nThis option is for those who don\'t like to waste space.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/new_options.jpg" alt="" title="new_options" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2219 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Slideshow Slugs </h3>\nYou can set custom slugs for slideshow post and taxonomies.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/slug.jpg" alt="" title="slug" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2028 imgborder" />\n\n\n[notification type="notification_info_tiny"] Other slideshow settings can be set when you <a href="">create slides</a>.[/notification]\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'Slideshow Settings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'slideshow-settings', '', '', '2012-08-28 23:05:27', '2012-08-28 23:05:27', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=2023', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (2025, 1, '2012-08-28 23:09:40', '2012-08-28 23:09:40', '[one_third]<br/> <br/><h2><strong>Blog Settings</strong></h2>\nIn Blog Settings you can set global layout settings for the blog posts and listings, and some more.<br/>\nTo edit Blog settings navigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> Blog</strong></span> page at your Dashboard.[/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions1.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1985 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n<br/>\n\n\n<h3>Blog Listing Sidebar Settings</h3>\n\nFirst two options controls position of sidebar for blog listings (blog, category, tag, search result, archive listings.) and which instance of sidebars to use. Our theme is scalable and can be used with or without sidebars.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/sidebar_blog.jpg" alt="" title="sidebar_blog" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2036 imgborder" />\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar position for blog listing</strong></span> - where the sidebar should be placed: at the left, right side or completely removed (full width).\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar for blog listing</strong></span> - select which of the sidebar you would like to use at blog page. You can learn how to create sidebar here: <a href="">Setup sidebars</a>\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Blog Posts Sidebar Settings</h3>\n\nSame as for the blog page, you can control position of sidebar for post page and set what instance of sidebars to use. Our theme scalable and can be used with or without sidebars.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/sidebar_post.jpg" alt="" title="sidebar_post" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2034 imgborder" />\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar position for single post</strong></span> - where the sidebar should be placed: at the left, right side or completely removed (full width).\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar for single post</strong></span> - select which of the sidebar you would like to use at single post page. You can learn how to create sidebar here: <a href="">Setup sidebars</a>\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n\n<h3>Additional</h3>\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Check to disable excerpts on blog listing</strong></span> - this option allow to swith from excerts to full content for blog listings.\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Disable author box</strong></span> - this option removes author box from post page.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/excerpts_authorbox.jpg" alt="" title="excerpts_authorbox" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2035 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/><br/>\n\n<h3>Options that was added in version 1.8</h3>\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Check to hide date for post </strong></span> - this option allow turn off square with date on the blog listing.\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Disable thumbnail for blog listing, categories, etc. </strong></span> - this option removes thumbnail from blog listings.\n<br/>\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/new_blog_options.jpg" alt="" title="new_blog_options" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2449 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'Blog Settings', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'blog-settings', '', '', '2015-05-06 21:37:22', '2015-05-06 13:37:22', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=2025', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (2039, 1, '2012-08-29 00:08:41', '2012-08-29 00:08:41', '[one_third]<br/> <br/><h2><strong>Testimonials Settings</strong></h2>\nIn Testimonials Settings you can set global layout settings for the testimonials posts and listings, and some more.<br/>\nTo edit Testimonials settings navigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> Testimonials</strong></span> page at your Dashboard.[/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions1.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1985 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n<br/>\n\n<h3>Testimonials Listing Sidebar Settings</h3>\nFirst two options controls position of sidebar for testimonials listings and which instance of sidebars to use. Our theme is scalable and can be used with or without sidebars.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/sidebar_listing.jpg" alt="" title="sidebar_listing" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2040 imgborder" />\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar position for testimonials listing</strong></span> - where the sidebar should be placed: at the left, right side or completely removed (full width).\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar for testimonials listing</strong></span> - select which of the sidebar you would like to use at testimonials page. You can learn how to create sidebar here: <a href="">Setup sidebars</a>\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Testimonials Posts Sidebar Settings</h3>\nSame as for the testimonials page, you can control position of sidebar for post page and set what instance of sidebars to use. Our theme scalable and can be used with or without sidebars.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/sidebar_post1.jpg" alt="" title="sidebar_post" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2041 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Testimonials Slugs </h3>\nYou can set custom slugs for testimonials post and taxonomies.\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/testimonial_slug.jpg" alt="" title="testimonial_slug" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2042 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'Testimonials Settings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'testimonials-settings', '', '', '2012-08-29 00:08:41', '2012-08-29 00:08:41', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=2039', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (2044, 1, '2012-08-29 00:09:52', '2012-08-29 00:09:52', ' [one_third] <br/><h2><strong>Sidebar Settings</strong></h2>\nWith the sidebar tab you can create custom sidebars to use throughout your pages and posts.<br/>\nTo create/delete sidebars navigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> Sidebars</strong></span> page at your Dashboard.[/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions1.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1985 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<h3>Adding a new sidebar</h3>\nSimply type name for your sidebar and click "<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Add sidebar</strong></span>".\nFor the sidebar names you are allowed to use uppercase, lowercase, numbers and underscores. Wordpress does not allow other characters or symbols so if you try to use them they will be stripped out.\n\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/add_sidebar.jpg" alt="" title="add_sidebar" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2045 imgborder" />\n\nAfter you created a new sidebar it will be listed below. You can always delete it by clicking delete button.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/sidebars_delete.jpg" alt="" title="sidebars_delete" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2046 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/><br/>\n\n [one_half]<h3>Using your new sidebar</h3>\n When editing your pages and posts there will be an option called "<strong>Sidebar</strong>" in "<strong>Layout Type</strong>" block. You can choose your custom sidebar here to use with that specific page or post.  [/one_half]   [one_half last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/layout.jpg" alt="" title="layout" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1656 imgborder" />  [/one_half]   [clear]\n\nAlso there is additional widget area between the map and content on pages. You can set custom sidebar for this area.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/underSidebar.jpg" alt="" title="underSidebar" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1649 imgborder" />\n\nAfter creating your custom sidebars you need to add some widgets to them.\n\nNavigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Appearance -> Widgets</strong></span> and you can find your new sidebars at the bottom of the list on the right side.\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'Sidebars Settings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'sidebars-settings', '', '', '2012-08-29 00:09:52', '2012-08-29 00:09:52', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=2044', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (2048, 1, '2012-08-29 00:11:44', '2012-08-29 00:11:44', '[one_third]<br/> <br/><h2><strong>Galleries Settings</strong></h2>\nIn Galleries Settings you can set global layout settings for the gallery posts and listings, and some more.<br/>\nTo edit Galleries settings navigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> Galleries</strong></span> page at your Dashboard.[/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions1.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1985 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n<br/>\n\n<h3>Galleries Listing Sidebar Settings</h3>\nFirst two options controls position of sidebar for Galleries listings and which instance of sidebars to use. Our theme is scalable and can be used with or without sidebars.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/gallery_sidebar_listing.jpg" alt="" title="gallery_sidebar_listing" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2051 imgborder" />\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar position for galleries listing</strong></span> - where the sidebar should be placed: at the left, right side or completely removed (full width).\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar for galleries listing</strong></span> - select which of the sidebar you would like to use at gallery listing page. You can learn how to create sidebar here: <a href="">Setup sidebars</a>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Gallery Posts Sidebar Settings</h3>\nYou can control position of sidebar for gallery post page and set what instance of sidebars to use. Our theme is scalable and can be used with or without sidebars.\n<br/>\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/gallery_post_sidebar.jpg" alt="" title="gallery_post_sidebar" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2050 imgborder" />\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar position for single gallery</strong></span> - where the sidebar should be placed: at the left, right side or completely removed (full width).\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Sidebar for single gallery</strong></span> - select which of the sidebar you would like to use at single gallery post page. You can learn how to create sidebar here: <a href="">Setup sidebars</a>\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Gallery Slugs </h3>\nYou can set custom slugs for gallery post and taxonomies.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/gallery_slug.jpg" alt="" title="gallery_slug" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2052 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Custom Icons for galery post listing</h3>\nOur theme comes with different icons, such as: plus, magnifier, text, microphone etc. They can be set near the title at gallery listing page to give more idea what inside of the gallery post. Using this option you can upload your own icons.\n<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/custom_icon.jpg" alt="" title="custom_icon" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2049 imgborder" />\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'Galleries settings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'galleries-settings', '', '', '2012-08-29 00:11:44', '2012-08-29 00:11:44', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=2048', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (2055, 1, '2012-08-29 00:13:42', '2012-08-29 00:13:42', '[one_third] <br/><h2><strong>Footer Settings</strong></h2>\nFooter tab holds options which are all about configuring your footer part of website, such as: widgets area, colors, footer text. Also this is where you can add your google analytics code. \n<br/>\nTo edit Footer settings navigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> Footer</strong></span> page at your Dashboard.[/one_third] \n[two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions1.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1985 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Footer widget area</h3>\nYou can have one widget area in footer with 1-4 columns. You can choose between how many columns you want by selecting number from "columns number for footer widget area" drop down. Columns will be stretched to cover the full width of footer area. I.E.: If you have a single widget it will be stretched to the full footer width, if you got 2 widgets, each of them will cover a 50% of a footer width.\n\nYou can disable the whole row of widgets in footer by switching off "Enable footer widget area" option.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/widget_area.jpg" alt="" title="widget_area" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2060 imgborder" />\n<br/>\nImage below shows you example of footer widget area with 4 columns.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/footer_widgets.jpg" alt="" title="footer_widgets" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2328 imgborder" />\n<br/>\nAt the image below you can see Footer colums sidebars in  <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Appearance->Widgets.</strong></span> This is where you need to place your widgets in order to see them in footer widget area.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/widgets.jpg" alt="" title="widgets" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2329 imgborder" />\n[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Footer text</h3> \nYou can setup your footer text (copyrights, disclamer, etc.), which is going to be shown on the left side of the footer.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/footer_text.jpg" alt="" title="footer_text" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2058 imgborder" />\n[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Google Analytics </h3>\nYou can add your Google Analytics code here.\nSign up for free at http://www.google.com/analytics/. After setting up your account you will be given a tracking code.\n<br/><img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/google_analytics.jpg" alt="" title="google_analytics" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2059 imgborder" />\n[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n\n [two_third] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/footer_colors_0.jpg" alt="" title="footer_colors_0" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2057 imgborder" /> \n [/two_third] \n [one_third last=last] <br/><br/><br/><h3>Footer colors options</h3> \nThis options allows you to choose colors for footer elements. <br/>\nThe image below shows what element control each color option from the image on the left.\n\nBut you can also change color and other settings for any element using "Custom Styles" section in "Theme Options". Check for the  needed code in <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/faq">"CSS Tweaks"</a> section of our <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/faq">FAQ</a>.\n<br/><br/><br/>\n[totop] to Top [/totop] \n [/one_third] \n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/footer_colors.jpg" alt="" title="footer_colors" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2056 imgborder" />\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>How to change other theme Colors?</h3>\nIf you need to change some other colors you can check <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/faq">CSS Tweaks</a> section in our <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/faq">FAQ</a>.', 'Footer Settings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'footer-settings', '', '', '2012-08-29 00:13:42', '2012-08-29 00:13:42', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=2055', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (2066, 1, '2012-08-30 21:21:58', '2012-08-30 21:21:58', '<br/><h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Introduction</strong></h2><br/>\n\nTheme was made for Wordpress 3.4 and newer versions. Make sure that you\'re not using version below 3.4, otherwise upgrade your Wordpress version if it is possible ( <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Updating_WordPress">http://codex.wordpress.org/Updating_WordPress</a> ).\n\nIn two words, you need to upload "Churchope" folder from our archive to your hosting into wp-content/themes directory (wp-content/themes/churchope that\'s how it should be look like). Or you can use "Install theme" function from dashboard and choose for upload "churchope.zip" that located at root of our archive. After that activate Theme from Wordpress admin panel by clicking " Themes" in "Appearance" section, which is located on the left side. After activation you\'ll be redirected to your theme settings page. More detailed instruction below.\n\n\n\n<br/><br/><br/>\n\n<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Installation:</strong></h2>\n<br/>\nFirst of all you choose the method which suits you most – via  WP dashboard or FTP.\n\nThe easier method is via WP dashboard but there are certain situations when it is impossible so we are going to name both.\n\n<br/>\n<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>1.</strong> </h1>\n<hr/>\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">Installation via FTP</h4><br/>\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>a)</strong></span> Use the simple download-extract scheme for the theme. There is an important point here: be sure you keep the original structure of the directories after decompressing the archive. Most often the authors of the theme add guidelines for installation. Follow them.\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>b)</strong></span> Most often a theme archive already contains needed structure of directories ready to upload your theme on your host web server after extracting.\n\nUpload to wp-content/themes/ folder with theme files on your host web server using an FTP client to access.\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>c)</strong></span> Transfer the extracted theme files.<br/><br/>\n\nThere are two ways of getting files onto your site, and once there, changing them.\n\nBy using your cPanel, or whatever file manager is provided by your host.\n\nBy using an FTP or SFTP client. You can learn how to use <a href="http://codex.wordpress.org/Using_FileZilla">FileZilla here</a>.\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/><br/>\n\n<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>2.</strong> </h1>\n<hr/>\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">Installation via WP  dashboard</h4><br/>\n\n\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>a)</strong></span> Installation of the Theme via WP dashboard starts naturally with logging on to the WP\nadministration panel.\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>b)</strong></span> Select “Appearances” at the left panel and then choose “Themes”.<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/appearance.jpg" alt="" title="appearance" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2086 imgborder" />\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>c)</strong></span> Click “Install Themes”.\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/install.jpg" alt="" title="install" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2087 imgborder" />\n\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>d)</strong></span> Press Upload in the upper sub menu to install downloaded earlier archive of your Theme.<br/>\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/upload.jpg" alt="" title="upload" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2088 imgborder" />\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n<br/><br/><h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>The final  step is Activation</strong></h2><br/>\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>1.</strong></span> Enter the  WP Administration Panel in your blog\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>2.</strong></span> Select the name or a screenshot of a Theme you wanted to activate in Appearances panel/Themes.<br/>\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/activate.jpg" alt="" title="activate" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2089 imgborder" />\n\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>3.</strong></span> A preview window with your theme will open. Check if it looks properly.\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>4.</strong></span> You will see  Save & Activate + name of your theme in the upper left corner.<br/>\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/preview.jpg" alt="" title="preview" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2090 imgborder" />\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>5.</strong></span> Activation complete.\n<br/>\n[notification type="notification_mark_tiny"]After installing theme you get clean WordPress installation. But our theme also comes with dummy content! Theme Options -> Dummy content[/notification]\n\n[notification type="notification_warning_tiny"]Warning! DO NOT INSTALL dummy data on your live website. It will corrupt your existing data. We suggest you install dumy data only on clean WordPress setup.[/notification] \n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<br/><h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Known problems when installing the theme</strong></h2><br/>\n\n<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>1.</strong> </h1>\n<hr/>\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">The “Broken theme and/or stylesheets missing” error is most common when you install or activate a new theme.</h4><br/>\n\nHowever that doesn’t necessarily mean that the theme was actually broken or the so important part is missing. It would  rather mean that the theme was just uploaded to the server incorrectly and missing <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>stylesheets are not missing but got to the wrong folder when downloading and unzipping</strong></span>.\n\nHere are some tips how to fix that:\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>a. After downloading and unzipping open the final theme folder. Inside there will be  the actual theme folder. The actual theme folder is where  the “ style.css” file is.</strong></span>\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>b. You must upload only the actual theme folder to your WordPress host. Our advice is to double check.</strong></span>\n\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>c. Enter your WordPress admin panel and activate your new theme.</strong></span>\n\nSumming up, the destination /wp-content/themes/themename/themename/style.css  is incorrect and is the reason of “ Broken theme and/or stylesheets missing” error message.\nIt  must look like /wp-content/themes/themename/style.css\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] \n\n<br/><br/>\n<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>2.</strong> </h1>\n<hr/>\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">Problems with uploading via WP admin panel due Upload limit.</h4><br/>\n\n\nYou may check your file upload limit on Your Media Uploader page in WordPress. Depending upon the web hosting company and the conditions of the service they provide it may vary. The most common is about 8 MB which is more or less enough. But uploading some media files like audio and video may become a problem with for example 2 MB upload limit.\n<br/>\nWe decided to share some tips about how to extend your maximum file upload size in WordPress:\n\n<br/>\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>1. Through functions.php file:</strong></span>\n\nYou may add the below mentioned code in the functions.php file of your theme\n\n\n<pre><code>@ini_set( \'upload_max_size\' , \'64M\' );\n@ini_set( \'post_max_size\', \'64M\');\n@ini_set( \'max_execution_time\', \'300\' );</code></pre>\n\n<br/>\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>2. Through PHP.INI file:</strong></span>\n\nIf you cannot see the php.ini file in your directory create the new one with below mentioned code and upload it to your root folder on your web server.\nIf you can see the php.ini file then change parameters or add :\n\n\n<pre><code>upload_max_filesize = 64M\npost_max_size = 64M \nmax_execution_time = 300</code></pre>\nIn case that tip does not work with 64MB, try it with 10MB.\n\n<br/>\n<span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>3. Through .htaccess method</strong></span>\n\nYou may try modifying the existing .htaccess file in the root directory or creating a new one.\nAdd the following code in the existing or new htacess file:\n\n\n<pre><code>php_value upload_max_filesize 64M \nphp_value post_max_size 64M \nphp_value max_execution_time 300 \nphp_value max_input_time 300</code></pre>\nYou can reset all of the setting for the each page on our custom panel by clicking "Reset" button on the bottom.\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'Theme Installation', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'theme-installation', '', '', '2012-08-30 21:21:58', '2012-08-30 21:21:58', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=2066', 0, 'page', '', 0),
