 (3270, 1, '2013-03-14 14:18:44', '2013-03-14 14:18:44', '[th-contact-form subject="from recaptcha form" captcha="1"] [th-contact-field label="Name" type="name" required="true" /] [th-contact-field label="Email" type="email" required="true" reply="true" /] [th-contact-field label="Website" type="url" /] [th-contact-field label="Comment" type="textarea" required="true" /] [/th-contact-form]', 'Contacts Page with reCaptcha', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'contacts-page-with-recaptcha', '', '', '2015-05-06 21:36:28', '2015-05-06 13:36:28', '', 22, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=3270', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (3297, 1, '2013-03-15 00:31:25', '2013-03-15 00:31:25', ' [one_third] <br/><h2><strong>reCaptcha</strong></h2>\nHere you can find options related to the reCaptcha used in contact form shortcode.<br/>\nTo edit reCaptcha settings navigate to <span style="color: #3d3d3d;"><strong>Theme Options -> reCaptcha</strong></span> page at your Dashboard. \n[notification type="notification_info_tiny"]This options is available starting version 1.12 of our theme.[/notification][/one_third] \n [two_third last=last] <img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/themeOptions1.jpg" alt="" title="themeOptions" class="alignright size-full wp-image-1985 imgborder" /> [/two_third] [clear]<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Abour Captcha</h3>\n<p>A CAPTCHA is a program that can tell whether its user is a human or a computer. You\'ve probably seen them — colorful images with distorted text at the bottom of Web registration forms. CAPTCHAs are used by many websites to prevent abuse from "bots," or automated programs usually written to generate spam. No computer program can read distorted text as well as humans can, so bots cannot navigate sites protected by CAPTCHAs.</p>\n<a href="http://www.google.com/recaptcha/learnmore">More info here</a>\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Add reCaptcha</h3>\n<p>You can add reCaptcha to your <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/online-documentation/contact-form-builder/">contact form</a>. To do this simply check "Use reCaptcha" when you add shortcode. But to make reCaptcha work you need to add private & public key first.</p>\n\n<br/><br/>\n<h3>Add Keys</h3>\n\nTo make reCaptcha work you need to add private & public key to the Theme Options -> reCaptcha and then click save.\n\n\nTo generate keys: \n\n1. Navigate to this page <a href="https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin/create?domains=churchope.themoholics.com&app=wordpress">Create a reCAPTCHA key</a>. \n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/generate_keys.jpg" alt="generate_keys" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3305 imgborder" />\n\n2. At this page add your domain in input and click "create key". \n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/key.jpg" alt="key" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3309 imgborder" />\n\n3. After that copy & paste generated key to the Theme Options -> reCaptcha.\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/recaptcha.jpg" alt="recaptcha" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3299 imgborder" />\n\n<br/>[totop] to Top [/totop] ', 'reCaptcha', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'recaptcha', '', '', '2013-03-15 00:31:25', '2013-03-15 00:31:25', '', 1866, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=3297', 0, 'page', '', 0),
 (3407, 1, '2013-03-20 01:36:26', '2013-03-20 01:36:26', '<br/><h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>reCaptcha</strong></h2>\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">Say No to Spam!</h4><br/>\n\n<p style="text-align:center;"> Our theme comes with integrated reCaptcha for contact form shortcode, what helps you protect your email from those annoying spam bots. </p>\n\n<br/><hr/><br/>\n\n<h4>Example</h4>\nYou can check contact form with recaptha <a href="http://churchope.themoholics.com/contacts-page-with-recaptcha/">here</a>.\n\n<img src="http://churchope.themoholics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/recaptcha_form.jpg" alt="recaptcha_form" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-3408 imgborder" />\n<br/>\n\n<h4>Abour Captcha</h4>\n\nA CAPTCHA is a program that can tell whether its user is a human or a computer. You’ve probably seen them — colorful images with distorted text at the bottom of Web registration forms. CAPTCHAs are used by many websites to prevent abuse from “bots,” or automated programs usually written to generate spam. No computer program can read distorted text as well as humans can, so bots cannot navigate sites protected by CAPTCHAs.\n\n<a href="http://www.google.com/recaptcha/learnmore">More info here</a>', 'reCaptcha', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'recaptcha', '', '', '2013-03-20 01:36:26', '2013-03-20 01:36:26', '', 20, 'http://churchope.themoholics.com/?page_id=3407', 0, 'page', '', 0),
